Description: A diamond is found in the jaw of a corpse discovered at a glass recycling plant; Booth learns that he has a medical issue; Hodgins thinks a ghost is following him.

Description: A black railroad worker is appointed sheriff of a town marked for destruction by a scheming politician.

Description: Opponents of Adam Schiff question the handling of a sexual-assault case by the police and the D.A.'s office.

Subject: Law & Order - Cherished
Description: The investigation into a girl's death reveals secrets the adoptive family was desperately trying to hide.

Description: Detectives discover a shocking twist involving unlikely suspects when they investigate the brutal beating of a black man dumped near the highway.

Description: Animals fight to survive extremes, from tundra to deserts, mountain summits to deep underground.

Description: Ziva and Gibbs head to a missing Marine's last-known whereabouts in Afghanistan; Tony's fears are revealed.

Subject: Playing Lessons From the Pros - Jenny Shin
Description: Jim ``Bones'' Mackay travels to Las Vegas to meet up with LPGA Tour winner Jenny Shin on the course for Part 1 of a 2-part series. Jenny shares her tips andstrategies that have led to her LPGA career of over a decade.

Subject: School of Golf - Chapter 14: The Open
Description: Martin Hall and Blair O'Neal teach the shots made famous by Open Champions at St. Andrews. Learn how to hit powerful draws like Tiger Woods, escape the rough like Seve Ballesteros, and stick wedges like John Daly.

Subject: School of Golf - Chapter 15: Power Up
Description: Martin Hall and Blair O'Neal teach how to maximize power like the game's longest drivers. Martin explains how baseball and boxing can translate into a more powerful golf swing.

Subject: School of Golf - Chapter 16: Right or Rubbish
Description: Martin Hall and Blair O'Neal teach the truth behind some of golf's greatest swing myths. Learn how to grip the club properly like Tiger Woods, hit more accurate irons like Padraig Harrington, and use Elvis Presley to add more distance.

Subject: School of Golf - Chapter 17: Play Like a Champion
Description: Martin Hall and Blair O'Neal teach the skills of golf's greatest champions; how to start the downswing like Jack Nicklaus and improve the swing path like Nick Faldo; guest Sophia Popov shares the drill that helped her win the 2020 AIG Women's Open.

Subject: School of Golf - Chapter 1: Golf's Most Important Skill
Description: Martin Hall and Blair O'Neal kick off the season by teaching the biggest keys to solid contact. Learn swing tips used by pros that will help improve ball striking. One of the best training aids for improving impact can be found in the kitchen.

Subject: School of Golf - Chapter 2: Short Game Secrets
Description: Martin Hall and Blair O'Neal teach the key shots needed to save strokes around the green. Learn wedge play tips used by Seve Ballesteros and a scrambling secret from Annika Sorenstam. Martin also teaches how to hit numerous other short game shots.

Subject: School of Golf - Chapter 3: Driving Distance
Description: Martin Hall and Blair O'Neal teach what to learn from the game's longest drivers past and present. Learn what Arnold Palmer did to maximize distance, a drill used by Rory McIlroy, and the swing keys of 2-time World Long Drive Champion Kyle Berkshire.

Subject: School of Golf - Chapter 4: Better Bunker Play
Description: Martin Hall and Blair O'Neal teach how to escape the sand like some of the game's all-time greats. Learn how to spin greenside bunker shots like Gary Player,cure one of the biggest short game faults with a Phil Mickelson move.

Subject: School of Golf - Chapter 5: Iconic Shots
Description: Martin Hall and Blair O'Neal teach how to recreate iconic shots hit by winners of the Arnold Palmer Invitational. Martin also shares tips to improve ball striking from Arnold Palmer.

Subject: School of Golf - Chapter 6: Slice Stoppers
Description: The biggest keys to stopping the slice and improving the backswing featuring a drill using a basketball and a tip from Nick Faldo. LPGA winner Matilda Castren demonstrates what she does in practice before every tournament to prevent slicing the ball.

Subject: School of Golf - Chapter 7: Putting Pointers
Description: Martin Hall and Blair O'Neal share putting pointers from the game's best players. Learn how to control speed on the greens like Tiger Woods, improve balance like Jack Nicklaus, square the putter face, and find the right putting grip.

Subject: School of Golf - Chapter 8: Majors Unclassified
Description: Martin Hall and Blair O'Neal share ball striking secrets from Masters Champions and Chevron Championship winners. Learn tips for working the ball used by Jack Nicklaus, Tiger Woods, Dustin Johnson, and Hideki Matsuyama.

Subject: 5 Clubs with Gary Williams
Description: Viewpoints of people in the game with people who love the game; we discuss what is of interest to them in the vast and deep reservoir of stories within the game of golf.

Subject: Fairways of Life with Matt Adams
Description: NY Times Best Selling Author and Golf Channel's Matt Adams brings you inside the ropes where you'll get all the latest headlines, exclusive interviews with all of golf's stars, equipment updates, instruction for your game and so much more.

Subject: College Football - Oklahoma at Tennessee
Description: The No. 18 Sooners (6-2, 2-2 SEC) seek revenge against the No. 14 Volunteers (6-2, 3-2). Tennessee topped Oklahoma 25-15 in 2024 in their first meeting as SEC rivals. The Vols are second among FBS programs in scoring at 45.6 points per game.

Subject: College Football - Kentucky at Auburn
Description: The Wildcats (2-5, 0-5 SEC) visit the Tigers (4-4, 1-4). Auburn snapped a three-game slide by outlasting Arkansas 33-24 on Oct. 25. Quarterback Jackson Arnold was benched in favor of Ashton Daniels, while teammate Jeremiah Cobb rushed for 153 yards.

Subject: College Football - South Carolina at Ole Miss
Description: The No. 7 Rebels (7-1, 4-1 SEC) host the Gamecocks (3-5, 1-5). Ole Miss rebounded from its first loss of 2025 with a 34-26 road victory over then-No. 13 Oklahoma. The Rebels won the last two meetings by a combined 41 points, including 27-3 in 2024.
